k to the seventh century. Some of the best-preserved post towns offer a real glimpse into the past, with wooden buildings lining stoned paths and the sound of watermills evoking a connection to those who have walked there centuries ago. Amongst the 69 post towns along this ancient trail, Magome, Tsumago and Narai stand out thanks to the conservation efforts made by the local government and people who have lived here for generations. With modern power lines and advertising boards being outlawed, the locals here have preserved the traditional townscape and unique history of this region.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:90%\"\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/nakasendo1-1666834720977.jpg\" width=\"300\" /\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/dsc02033-1666834651573.jpg\" width=\"300\" /\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/dsc01930-1666834754918.jpg\" width=\"300\" /\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 style=\"text-align:center\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:20px\"\u003eHighlights of The Nakasendō Trail\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eWhile portions of the trail have been converted to roads and railways, there are still some well-preserved sections that wind through bamboo forests, fields and along rivers and streams; our tours include hiking on these parts of the trail with accommodation nights in small family-run \u003cem\u003eminshuku\u003c/em\u003e and \u003cem\u003eryokan\u003c/em\u003e. The natural beauty of this region has long inspired many writers and artists and we hope that our guests are moved by the unique culture, architecture, cuisine and local people as well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eVisit the bio-diverse national parks of Kamikōchi and Oku-Hida.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eKamikōchi, in the western region of Nagano prefecture, is located in the Azusa River Valley and surrounded by dramatic mountain scenery. Walking in this area is a fantastic experience especially during the autumn foliage season.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eOku-Hida also offers stunning views of the Northern Japan Alps and is particularly renowned for their \u003cem\u003erotenburo\u003c/em\u003e (露天風呂/outdoor baths).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","hightlight":"","information":"","secure_safe":"","type":1,"level":{"1":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"2":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"3":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"4":{"thumbnail":"","text":""}},"is_active":1,"is_delete":0,"created_at":"2022-08-05T01:56:50.782Z","updated_at":"2024-04-02T02:49:13.621Z","created_by":"","updated_by":"","subtitle":"","region":2},{"uuid":"41126343-8bb3-4cbb-b494-677226094889","name":"Kumano Kodo Trail","code":"IBKumanoKodo","slug":"kumano-kodo","sequence":2,"thumbnail":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kumano-1675836291103.jpg","overview":"","gallery":[{"name":"Kumano-Nachi.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kumanonachi-1662686193928.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Kumano-trail1.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kumanotrail1-1662686200059.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Kumano-view.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kumanoview-1662686203343.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Kumano-view2.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kumanoview2-1662686209762.jpg",