03cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eTake a boat to the art island of Naoshima to visit the many museums and Kusama Yayoi\u0026rsquo;s famous pumpkins.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eRelive the creation myth of Japan at Izumo Grand Shrine, one of Japan\u0026rsquo;s oldest and most prominent Shintō shrines. Enshrined here is Ōkuninushi-no-Ōkami, the deity said to have created the land of Japan and pulled it from the sea.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","hightlight":"","information":"","secure_safe":"","type":1,"level":{"1":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"2":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"3":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"4":{"thumbnail":"","text":""}},"is_active":1,"is_delete":0,"created_at":"2022-08-05T01:58:50.752Z","updated_at":"2024-04-02T02:23:45.932Z","created_by":"","updated_by":"","subtitle":"","region":2},{"uuid":"20da8cc2-b46d-4cc7-9499-eb3f1bfe39eb","name":"Kyushu","code":"IBKyushu","slug":"kyushu","sequence":9,"thumbnail":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kyushu-1675836678578.jpg","overview":"","gallery":[{"name":"Kyushu-waterfall.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kyushuwaterfall-1662682608673.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Kyushu-view.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kyushuview-1662682613293.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Kyushu-trail.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kyushutrail-1662682619122.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Kyushu-town.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kyushutown-1662682623059.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Kyushu-pond.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kyushupond-1662682632846.jpg","focal":null}],"short_description":"\u003cp\u003eKyūshū is the third largest of the islands that comprise the Japanese archipelago and is easily accessible via boat, plane or train. The island itself is popular for its temperate climate as it maintains a few additional degrees of warmth compared to other parts of mainland Japan. Whether a city dweller, adventure traveller, hot spring enthusiast or even simply a lover of Japanese anime, Kyūshū serves as an idyllic destination for any traveller to Japan searching for something new.\u003c/p\u003e\n","long_description":"\u003ch2 style=\"text-align:center\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:20px\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFUKUOKA, NAGASAKI, BEPPU AND MORE\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eKyūshū\u0026nbsp;is the third largest of the islands that comprise the Japanese archipelago and is easily accessible via boat, plane or train. The island itself is popular for its temperate climate as it maintains a few additional degrees of warmth compared to other parts of mainland Japan. It also offers an equally vast array of scenery ranging from built up cityscapes to luxuriant hot-spring resorts, rich with greenery. The hub of most transportation on to and off of the island is the city of\u0026nbsp;Fukuoka, which sits towards the north. Within Fukuoka sits one of the most compact districts in the world,\u0026nbsp;Hakata, hosting an international airport, train stations and a port, all packed into a small 2.5-kilometer radius. Whether a city dweller, adventure traveller, hot spring enthusiast or even simply a lover of Japanese anime, Kyūshū serves as an idyllic destination for any traveller to Japan searching for something new.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:90%\"\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/kagoshima20130307_055-1667894888478.jpg\" width=\"300\" /\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/yakushima20130310_230-1667895045390.jpg\" width=\"300\" /\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/nagasaki_20121125_0011-1667894939148.jpg\" width=\"300\" /\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 style=\"text-align:center\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:20px\"\u003eHighlights of Kyūshū Island\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eTravelling slightly west from the entry hub of Fukuoka will take visitors to the historically iconic landmark of Nagasaki, which played a major role in foreign trade with the rest of the world. Then, following the curve of the island back to the east sits Ōita Prefecture and one of Japan\u0026rsquo;s most well-known hot spring resorts, Beppu, with its affectionately named \u0026#39;Hells\u0026#39; collection of hot springs. Those searching away from the built up areas don\u0026rsquo;t have to look too far, with Mount Aso sitting steadfast in the island\u0026rsquo;s centre and Yakushima floating nearby the island\u0026#39;s southern coast.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eDine at the streetside \u003cem\u003eyatai\u003c/em\u003e (屋台/food stands) which serve as a focal point of Fukuoka\u0026rsquo;s unique food culture; either draped in plastic tarpaulin in the cooler seasons to cocoon the patrons in warmth, or left open to allow the sea breeze to cool them down.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eDiscover the Hells of Beppu that dot the city districts with their assortment of vivid colours, from sea blue to blood red. Evidenced by their bubbling surface, these aren\u0026#39;t used for bathing, but can be put to good use for making soft-boiled eggs instead.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eStroll through the man-made port island of Dejima in Nagasaki and its impressive architectural style, influenced by Danish traders. Then travel north to visit the tranquil Nagasaki Peace Park which commemorates the city\u0026rsquo;s history and those who lost their lives in Japan\u0026#39;s second atomic bombing.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eBrave an active volcano by climbing to Aso\u0026rsquo;s caldera - considered to be one of the largest in the world with a circumference of 100 kilometres. Sometimes the area is closed to visitors due to an increase of the volcano\u0026rsquo;s toxic fumes or potential for volcanic activity.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli style=\"text-align:justify\"\u003eTravel by boat or by plane to the subtropical island of Yakushima and its cedar forests and its trees said to be more than 7000 years old. Regular rainfall creates a misty shroud that permeates the island, famously inspiring the setting for Hayao Miyazaki\u0026rsquo;s archetypal animated movie \u003cem\u003ePrincess Mononoke\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","hightlight":"","information":"","secure_safe":"","type":1,"level":{"1":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"2":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"3":{"thumbnail":"","text":""},"4":{"thumbnail":"","text":""}},"is_active":1,"is_delete":0,"created_at":"2022-08-05T01:59:43.466Z","updated_at":"2024-04-02T02:14:44.38Z","created_by":"","updated_by":"","subtitle":"","region":2},{"uuid":"98c6411c-a298-44fb-aaef-2890f68b9940","name":"Kanto (Tokyo, Nikko, Hakone)","code":"IBKanto","slug":"kanto","sequence":10,"thumbnail":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/kanto-1675836353670.jpg","overview":"","gallery":[{"name":"Nikko-lake.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/nikkolake-1662688286313.jpg","focal":null},{"name":"Nikko-temple.jpg","url":"https://static-oku.diqit.io/uploads/oku/destinations/nikkotemple-1662688290315.jpg","focal":nu